snippet.textDisplay:
Here's what I'm going to do ASAP if I'm Tim Cook:

1. Aquire Leica and cut it loose from Huawei.

2. Bring a professional camera app "Leica Cam" pre-installed with iOS, with a full manual mode and cool Leica filters.

3. Make some room for Leica cameras and lenses in Apple Stores.

Here's why:

1. It's the algorithm and color style that matters most in smart phone photography. Leica has the best style (also top lenses) and Apple has the rest. Without Leica, Huawei (along with other companies) will be forced to throw even more money on hardware specs, which is much less efficient.

2. iPhone lacks a cool & professional cam mode to shut many mouths.

3. Leica's brand value and customer base fits Apple's much better than it fits Huawei's. Huawei's brand value relies half on it's 5G tech, and half on the Leica camera, which is the major soft spot.

Huawei would be a fool trying to win the ecosystem war, but if it ever came back from the ongoing situation, A NIGHTMARE for Apple.

snippet.textDisplay:
You made mistake on begging of the video. Maximu resolution is 3200x1440 60Hz.
Also, I don't know why all reviews write specs as "1440p 120Hz" display. It's NOT TRUE. And, it's unfair towards other brands that really have it (like OnePlus). In other markets, like TVs or computer monitors, that panels can achieve huge refresh rates on low resolutions (like 800x600) and much lower on native. Nobody advertise it with native resolution + refresh rate on low resolution. That way you can sell most 4K TVs as 4K 120Hz...

EDIT: This review is not that good at all. Galaxy Mega is gigantic comparing to S20 Ultra because, you guess, aspect ratio (and bezels ofc).
